HEADWORD: merchantry
<hw>mer"chant*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
body of merchants taken collectively; <as>as, the <ex>merchantry</ex> of
a country</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The business of a merchant; merchandise.</def>
<rj><au>Walpole.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Merciable</ent>⟦br⟧
